# Participating in the PR Review Debate from Cursor

The CI review pipeline posts inline comments and then has a programmer agent argue back automatically. But you (the human developer) can also participate in the debate directly from Cursor.

## Fetch the current debate state

Before doing anything, load the live state of the review:

```bash
PR=$(gh pr view --json number --jq .number)
REPO=ykita0224-work/hive-strategy

# All review comments (reviewer findings)
gh api repos/$REPO/pulls/$PR/comments \
  --jq '.[] | select(.in_reply_to_id == null) | {id: .id, path: .path, line: .line, body: .body}'

# All reply threads (programmer agent verdicts)
gh api repos/$REPO/pulls/$PR/comments \
  --jq '.[] | select(.in_reply_to_id != null) | {reply_to: .in_reply_to_id, body: .body}'
```

## How to manually argue against a comment

If the programmer agent accepted a comment but you disagree (false positive), post a reply:

```bash
gh api repos/ykita0224-work/hive-strategy/pulls/comments/<COMMENT_ID>/replies \
  --method POST \
  --field body="💬 **[Human Override — ARGUE]** <your explanation here>"
```

Replace `<COMMENT_ID>` with the ID from the fetch above.

## How to force-accept a comment the agent argued away

If the agent argued but you agree with the reviewer, post a reply and then fix manually:

```bash
gh api repos/ykita0224-work/hive-strategy/pulls/comments/<COMMENT_ID>/replies \
  --method POST \
  --field body="✅ **[Human Override — ACCEPT]** Fixing this — the reviewer is correct."
```

Then fix the code, commit, and push. The CI loop will re-review.

## How to dismiss all remaining comments and close the loop

If you are satisfied that remaining issues are false positives or intentional:

```bash
PR=$(gh pr view --json number --jq .number)
gh pr review $PR --comment --body "All remaining review comments have been addressed or intentionally dismissed. Ready for merge."
```

## Cursor — what to do when the user says "argue against this"

1. Fetch the PR comments to find the specific comment ID
2. Read the file at the referenced path and line to understand the code
3. Draft a clear technical argument for why the code is correct
4. Post the reply via the `gh api` command above
5. Report back what you argued and why

## Cursor — what to do when the user says "accept and fix this"

1. Fetch the comment body to understand the issue
2. Read the full file at the referenced path
3. Apply the fix directly in Cursor
4. Post an acceptance reply via the `gh api` command above
5. Commit and push — the CI loop will verify

## Debate etiquette

- Be specific in arguments — vague "this is intentional" replies are not useful
- If arguing, explain the invariant, contract, or trade-off that makes the code correct
- If accepting, say what you are fixing and why the reviewer was right
- The goal is a correct codebase, not winning the argument
